&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced &lt;strong&gt;Claims Management &amp;amp; Coverage Counsel&lt;/strong&gt; to join our growing national team. This attorney will play a key role in providing sophisticated claims management, insurance coverage analysis, and strategic risk assessment across a broad range of specialty and professional liability lines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will independently manage complex claims and coverage matters from inception through resolution, partnering closely with clients, carriers, and outside counsel to develop effective litigation, settlement, and risk mitigation strategies. This position offers the opportunity to work on high-exposure, challenging matters while collaborating with a nationally recognized team of insurance professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a remote or hybrid position that may be based in any state where Wilson Elser has an office.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independently manage a claims caseload, from claim notification through resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate coverage, liability and damages issues for complex professional liability, employment liability, real estate liability, miscellaneous liability and D&amp;amp;O matters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft reservation of rights and coverage denial letters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively monitor claims, prepare and develop handling and resolution strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assign, coordinate, and manage outside counsel to obtain optimal resolutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare reports for clients with exposure analysis and reserve recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resolve claims through direct negotiations and participation in mediation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with other attorneys and Partners on legal projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to regularly interface with clients, carriers and outside counsel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;JD from an accredited Law School&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Licensed to practice law in at least one U.S. jurisdiction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of legal practice experience in the insurance area.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience handling complex insurance claims and evaluating coverage issues across professional and specialty liability lines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience drafting coverage opinions, reservation of rights letters, and coverage denial letters is strongly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience

